%pyspark
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

##Generate data
#Simulation
N=5

Y=np.random.randint(0,2,N)
X=np.array([np.random.normal(0,1,N)+Y*np.random.normal(3,1,N), np.random.normal(0,1,N)+Y*np.random.normal(3,1,N) ])

#plot data
plt.scatter(X[0], X[1], c=Y)
plt.show()

%pyspark
X_par=sc.parallelize(np.transpose(X)).zipWithIndex().map(lambda(x,y) : (y,x) )
Y_par=sc.parallelize(np.transpose(Y)).zipWithIndex().map(lambda(x,y) : (y,x) )
print(X_par.collect())
print(Y_par.collect())
Y_X= Y_par.join(X_par).map(lambda(y,x) : LabeledPoint(x[0], x[1])  )
print(Y_X.collect())
print(Y_X.map(lambda x: x.label).collect() )
print(Y_X.map(lambda x: x.features.toArray()).collect() )

lamb=0.5
Y_K=construct_K_lab(Y_X,sc.parallelize(np.transpose(X)),lamb)

construct_labeled(Y_K[0],Y_K[1])[0].collect()

%pyspark
#Example Logistic Regression

from pyspark.mllib.regression import LabeledPoint

Y_K=construct_K(sc.parallelize(np.transpose(Y)),sc.parallelize(np.transpose(X)),sc.parallelize(np.transpose(X)),0.5)


l_train=construct_labeled(Y_K[0], Y_K[1])[0]


# Evaluating the model on training data
from pyspark.mllib.classification import LogisticRegressionWithLBFGS, LogisticRegressionModel

LogitModel = LogisticRegressionWithLBFGS.train(l_train)
labelsAndPreds = l_train.map(lambda p: (p.label, LogitModel.predict(p.features)))
trainErr = labelsAndPreds.filter(lambda lp: lp[0] != lp[1]).count() / float(l_train.count())
print("Training Error = " + str(trainErr))

#Example SVM
from pyspark.mllib.classification import SVMModel, SVMWithSGD

SVMModel = SVMWithSGD.train(l_train)
labelsAndPreds = l_train.map(lambda p: (p.label, SVMModel.predict(p.features)))
trainErr = labelsAndPreds.filter(lambda lp: lp[0] != lp[1]).count() / float(l_train.count())
print("Training Error = " + str(trainErr))


#Example Ridge Regression
from pyspark.mllib.regression import LinearRegressionModel, LinearRegressionWithSGD

RidgeModel = LinearRegressionWithSGD.train(l_train)
labelsAndPreds = l_train.map(lambda p: (p.label, RidgeModel.predict(p.features)))
trainErr = labelsAndPreds.filter(lambda lp: abs(lp[0] - lp[1])>0.5 ).count() / float(l_train.count())
print("Training Error = " + str(trainErr))
